article.headline: Utah St. 77, Montana-Western 58
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Jaycee Carroll scored 31 points to lead Utah State to a 77-58 win over Montana-Western on Monday night. It was the fifth career 30-point game for Carroll, who also had a team-high seven rebounds. Gary Wilkinson scored 12 for the Aggies (2-1). Western (1-5) was led in scoring by Gus McDonald with a career-high 19 points, the only Bulldog in double figures. Aaron Sims, leading scorer for Western at 10.4 points, was held to two points. Utah State also forced 27 turnovers and was credited with 14 steals, led by Desmond Stephens with five. Consecutive 3-point shots by the Bulldogs made the score 54-45 six minutes into the second half. But Western was never able to get that close again, as the Aggies stretched the lead to 20 points. In the first half, USU burst out to an 11-point lead. Western cut the lead to 20-23 with 5:30 to play, but a steal and layup by Stephens stopped the Bulldogs' momentum. Aided by a half-court shot by Kris Clark as the horn sounded, USU led 39-27 at halftime.
